   6> Github releases 

 = A Github release is the official published version
   of a project based on a git tag.


  # Git tag or github release
 
  Gt tag
 
 > Gives a version name to a specific commit.

 > example = git tag v1.0

  push tag

 > git push origin --v1.0 = upload the tag to the remote github repository.


  Github release
  
 = A github release officially publishes a tagged version with release notes.


  # Release workflow

Project Completed
        ↓
Create Tag
        ↓
Push Tag
        ↓
Create GitHub Release
        ↓
Write Release Notes
        ↓
Publish Release

